Package: nbstitch
Type: Package
Title: Topological Repair and Infrastructure Augmentation for Spatial Neighborhood Graphs
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person(
      "Prince", "Oppong Boakye",
      email = "poppongb@uni-muenster.de",
      role = c("aut", "cre")
    )
  )
Description: Provides a programmatic toolkit to repair and augment fragmented spatial 
    adjacency neighborhood graphs (specifically 'nb' objects from the 'spdep' 
    package) to reach a single connected topological component. Ensuring a single 
    connected component is critical for satisfying the strict mathematical 
    sum-to-zero constraints required by Bayesian Gaussian Markov Random Field 
    (GMRF) spatial priors, such as intrinsic CAR or BYM2 models in 'R-INLA'. 
    Implements a modular multi-stage engineering workflow: injecting 
    coordinate-based infrastructure edges ('add_wormhole'), running iterative 
    nearest-neighbor component merging ('sweep_absorp'), and resolving true 
    spatial isolates ('stitch_island'). Validates coordinate structures to 
    enforce projected coordinate systems (e.g., UTM), ensuring robust 
    underlying Euclidean distance metrics.
